Done. Phase 1 interaction unification complete.

**What changed (base.html only, plus one stale comment):**
- Deleted three separate paths (select-then-click, arm-then-click, drag) → one state machine: `armSource(el)` sets the armed source; `resolveTarget(slotEl)` toggles picked own-slots; both click and drag call the same two functions.
- Select mode gone — no more `.selected` toggle / `selectedSlots()`. Own slots now `.picked`.
- Multi-swap is now a **post-drop confirm**: pick one slot → floating `#swap-bar` appears → tap more slots → Confirm posts `multiswap-*` (2+) or plain `swap`/`take` (1). Server API untouched.
- Auto-arm: clicking/dropping on a slot with nothing armed grabs the sole `.armable` (there's never more than one), so arming is implicit.
- Reset on SSE re-render via `htmx:afterSwap`.

**Couldn't verify:** `go build ./...` requires an approval this non-interactive session can't grant. Changes are pure JS/CSS inside `{{define}}` blocks — no Go, no template directives touched — so the build compiles unchanged code. Run `go build ./...` to confirm.

